      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THREE GRAND (1) comes through a strong form race last time out at Albany where she was beaten 2.5L. This is an easier assignment today though and while the drop in distance is a query, she may just be too classy for this field. MANTA RAY BAY (2) turned in a solid performance at York last time out. Drawn well again today and the booking of Yuill is a good push for her chances. Can build on what she did last time out. CLASSIC ROYALE (4) is on the quick turnaround from York on Monday where he was narrowly defeated in a similar race. Should get every chance again today from the inside barrier and he can make an impression as he reaches peak fitness. I'M EUGENE (6) is another on the quick turnaround and is not to be discounted with no weight on his back. PRECAST (3) was beaten 3.5 lengths into fourth in a 1200m contest at York last time out. No surprise to see her in the frame.",
